      h2 Sushi Making
      p The children really love to cook and they get huge satisfaction from eating the treats they make themselves! 
      p We make all sorts of dishes, from Santa cupcakes to tiger-shaped pizzas, but one of the most popular cooking tasks is making sushi. We prepare a variety of veggies in separate bowls so the children can design their own perfect combination to make their sushi unique. Here are some ideas and instructions of #[a(href='https://www.taste.com.au/recipes/sushi-kids/ba9ef322-8c95-4d4a-a364-1b8c6448efec') how to make sushi at home with your children].  
    
    section
      h2 Science Experiments
      p The children love nothing more than becoming scientists! They’re forever asking us to come up with new, creative science experiments for them to investigate.
      p Here’s how to make #[a(href='https://www.google.co.uk/amp/s/m.wikihow.com/Make-Elephant-Toothpaste%3famp=1') elephant’s toothpaste], an experiment where a chemical reaction causes thick foam to shoot out of a bottle! It’s easy and loads of fun! 
      p Another popular one is #[a(href='https://www.homesciencetools.com/article/how-to-make-a-homemade-lava-lamp-science-project/') homemade lava lamps]; all you need to make a lava lamp is vegetable oil, food colouring, water and an Alka-Seltzer... the results are mesmerising! 

    p
      em What are your favourite creative activities for children? We’d love to hear your ideas and maybe try them out at our clubs. #[a(href=facebook.site) Let us know your thoughts on Facebook]!
